t199.description:
Implement `TaintTracker` — combines static taint via `jfc-graph`'s `taint` DSL op with LLM-discovered source/sink specs (Multi-Agent Taint Specification Extraction, arXiv 2601.10865).

**Two-phase approach (LLMVD.js):**

**Phase 1 — Spec discovery (one-time per project, cached in `.jfc/audit/taint_specs.json`):**
Spawn an `agent_taint_speccer` that scans the project's public API and external boundaries, emits a JSON spec:
```json
{
  "sources": [
    { "handle": "fn:server::handle_request", "param": "body", "kind": "UserInput" },
    { "handle": "fn:env::var", "ret": "AnyOf", "kind": "Environment" }
  ],
  "sinks": [
    { "handle": "fn:std::process::Command::new", "param": "program", "kind": "CommandInjection" },
    { "handle": "fn:std::fs::read_to_string", "param": "path", "kind": "PathTraversal" }
  ],
  "sanitizers": [
    { "handle": "fn:validation::sanitize_path", "kind": "PathTraversal" }
  ]
}
```

**Phase 2 — Flow tracing:**
For each `(source, sink)` pair, run `graph_query("fn:source | taint \"<param>\" | depth 10")` and check if `sink` appears in the result. If yes, emit a `TaintedSink` finding with the full taint chain.

Sanitizers break the chain: if a sanitizer node sits on the path, drop that path. (Mirrors LLMVD.js's PoC validation loop where sanitized paths can't be exploited.)

API:
```rust
pub struct TaintTracker<'g> { graph: &'g CodeGraph, specs: TaintSpecs }
impl TaintTracker<'_> {
    pub async fn discover_specs(&mut self, provider: Arc<dyn Provider>, model: ModelId) -> Result<()>;
    pub fn trace(&self, source: &SymbolHandle, sink_kind: SinkKind) -> Vec<TaintChain>;
}
```

**Tests:** `_normal` (LLM mock returns one source + one sink → chain found through 3 hops), `_robust` (LLM returns malformed JSON → no panic, empty spec, graceful skip).

t208.description:
Add module `crates/jfc-ui/src/plan.rs` (mirrors existing `memory.rs` shape) with:

```rust
pub struct Plan {
    pub path: PathBuf,                    // .jfc/plans/<slug>.md
    pub frontmatter: PlanFrontmatter,
    pub body: String,                     // the structured plan markdown (plan_template-shaped)
}

pub struct PlanFrontmatter {
    pub slug: String,                     // url-safe identifier
    pub title: String,
    pub status: PlanStatus,               // Draft | Active | Paused | Done | Archived
    pub level: PlanLevel,                 // User | Project | Team  (matches MemoryLevel)
    pub scope: PlanScope,                 // Private | Team
    pub created: Option<String>,          // ISO8601
    pub last_advanced: Option<String>,    // last time progress was recorded
    pub linked_task_ids: Vec<String>,     // jfc TaskStore IDs
    pub supersedes: Option<String>,       // slug of older plan this replaces
    pub tags: Vec<String>,                // free-form labels for filtering
}

pub enum PlanStatus { Draft, Active, Paused, Done, Archived }
```

`PlanStore` API (mirrors `TaskStore` interface):
```rust
pub struct PlanStore { root: PathBuf, index: Mutex<HashMap<String, Plan>> }
impl PlanStore {
    pub fn open_project(git_root: Option<&Path>) -> Result<Arc<Self>>;
    pub fn create(&self, title: &str, body: &str) -> Result<Plan>;
    pub fn get(&self, slug: &str) -> Option<Plan>;
    pub fn list(&self, filter: PlanFilter) -> Vec<Plan>;
    pub fn update(&self, slug: &str, patch: PlanPatch) -> Result<Plan>;
    pub fn advance(&self, slug: &str, summary: &str) -> Result<Plan>;  // appends to "## Progress Log"
    pub fn archive(&self, slug: &str, reason: &str) -> Result<()>;
    pub fn reload_if_changed(&self) -> bool;   // hot-reload on user-edited file
}
```

Persistence: each plan is `.jfc/plans/<slug>.md` with frontmatter parseable by the existing `crate::memory::parse_frontmatter` helper (extract or refactor it). Maintain `.jfc/plans/index.json` for fast list/filter without reading every file. Atomic writes via tempfile+rename (precedent: `task_store.rs::persist`).

**Tests:** `_normal` (create, list, get, update, archive round-trip), `_robust` (corrupt frontmatter → fallback defaults, no panic; concurrent process writes → reload picks up changes).

t202.description:
Gate every candidate finding through `paths entry -> suspicious_point` query. Findings without a path are dropped (or downgraded to Info severity if user passes `--include-unreachable`).

API:
```rust
pub struct ReachabilityProver<'g> { graph: &'g CodeGraph, entrypoints: Vec<SymbolHandle> }
impl ReachabilityProver<'_> {
    pub fn prove(&self, target: &SymbolHandle) -> Option<Vec<SymbolHandle>>;
    pub fn prove_with_preconditions(&self, target: &SymbolHandle) -> Option<ReachabilityProof>;
}

pub struct ReachabilityProof {
    pub path: Vec<SymbolHandle>,
    pub preconditions: Vec<Precondition>,
    pub entrypoint_kind: EntryPointKind,
    pub depth: usize,
}
```

Uses `graph_query("path fn:entry -> fn:target")` for shortest, falls back to `paths` for all-simple within depth budget. For preconditions, uses the existing `preconditions` DSL operator.

**Critical:** an unreachable finding is the mythos failure mode. This is what makes jfc-audit better — it never reports a bug that no public caller can hit.

For findings inside trait impls or generics, also check `possible_types` to confirm at least one concrete type can flow there.

**Tests:** `_normal` (3 entrypoints, target reachable via 2 → returns shortest, preconditions captured), `_robust` (unreachable target returns None; finding gets dropped upstream).
